be operational by the end of the year. The other two, Rasgas and
Enron/QGPC are still at the planning stage. The foreign partners in
Qatargas are MOBIL (United States), TOTAL (France) and the Japanese
companies MITSUI and MARUBENI, and outlets have already been secured in
Japan for all Qatargas production. Rasgas, in which Mobil has a 30% stake,
has thus far placed only a quarter of maximum projected production in
South Korea. Finally, the American company ENRON and QGPC are expected to
finalise an agreement to build a third gas liquefaction plant later this
year. Enron plans to market production in Israel, Jordan and India.

