Got a breakthrough? A better widget, perhaps? How

Got a breakthrough? A better widget, perhaps? How
about "the world's most efficient ultra-
capacitance fiber nickel metal electric chassis
flywheel CNG cylinder"? A photosatifor? Or even a
better Johnson rod? Calstart's Project hatchery
wants to hear from you. "Project Hatchery is an
incubator for small businesses with big ideas,"
the California alternative transportation
consortium says. Project Hatchery promises access
to affordable office and prototype fabrication
space (including computer design systems),
marketing via the Internet, help with tracking
down funding sources, and a "knowledge base of
140+ private and public participants."
Calstart/Project Hatchery, Glen Perry, 818-565-
5600; fax 818-565-5610.




