Toyota has picked a 1,100-acre site in Princeton,

Toyota has picked a 1,100-acre site in Princeton,
Ind. -- 21 miles north of Evansville -- as the
location for its fourth North American vehicle
assembly plant. Workers at the new $700-million
facility are to begin building the T100 truck,
which is currently produced in Japan, in the fall
of 1998. The Princeton plant will employ
approximately 1,300 people turning out 100,000
vehicles a year. The T100 will use a new V8
engine. Toyota Motor Corporate Services of North
America, 212-223-0303.




