<A NAME = "3"></A>Copyright
INTERNATIONAL COAL REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

NATPOWER BUYS FOUR CAPES

National Power of the UK has booked four capes from the US for first
quarter delivery, bringing to well in excess of 1mt the company has
booked for 1996 delivery just from the US. The purchases, of mid-
sulphur material, have all been done a few cents higher than similar
purchases by the company in the Fall of 1995. They have helped to
produce a drying up of supplies of this quality coal from some US
suppliers. One cape is from the East Coast from AMCI - which had
already won 500,000t worth of business from NatPower; the balance is
coming through traders from the Gulf.



