INTERNATIONAL COAL REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

CHILGENER SETTLES 500,000T

Chilgener has settled a third of its 1.5mt requirement for 1996,
concluding with Colombian producers at competitive prices. Sources say
the buyer claims to have concluded at $34.00-35.00/t FOB basis 6,600kc
GAR.

The company plans to conduct talks with other suppliers over the next
month. It has inventories sufficient to last it until March and can
wait to conclude until late February.

Meanwhile, the Chilean utility has asked for bids on one or two trial
cargoes of western US and western Canadian coals. Offers are due
January 10. Observers say the company is looking to diversify supply
sources, given the rapid growth in its consumption.



