January 5, 1996

KEPCO FIXES OVER 1MT

South Korean utility Korea Electric Power Co has booked eight, option a
ninth, capes with compatriot owner Samsun to trade from Newcastle. It
agreed a rate of $6.50 for shipments of 120-132,000t and expects them
to be made over a year from February. Samsun is now in the market for
time charter tonnage to work the business on a consecutive voyage
basis.



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
