AUSTRALIA SHIPS 137MT

A survey of port throughput in Australia shows that the country lifted
exports from 131.2mt to 136.7mt. Port Kembla was the only port to see a
significant fall, dropping 1.5mt to 10.8mt. Four ports moved over 20mt -
 Gladstone, Hay Point, Dalrymple Bay and Newcastle which rose 3.4mt to
48.9mt.

The stock situation tightened during November, largely through
industrial action, cutting exports stocks from 11.5mt to 11.5mt. A
further fall was predicted for December because of production problems
in Queensland caused by high rainfall. All the fall was in coking coal
which dropped 1.2mt.

