INTERNATIONAL GAS REPORT via NewsNet
January 5, 1996

NORFRA GROUP URGES SHORT LOOP

A 15-20 km by-pass loop linking Norway's Statpipe and Norpipe gas
trunklines around the Ekofisk centre, should replace the existing
connection via the North Sea field, according to state oil and gas firm
Statoil. It has put the proposal forward as operator of the NorFra
partnership planning a gasline from Norway to Dunkirk, France. A
government decision is expected by 1 March.

Costed at NKr500m ($79.14m), the short loop is preferred by NorFra
partners to a longer 150 km alternative, said Statoil. Due ready by
summer 1998, it will feed gas from fields including Statfjord and
Gullfaks into the Norpipe line to Emden. Completion will coincide with
completion of new facilities at Ekofisk which will in future handle gas
from Ekofisk alone.



