January 5, 1996

TIGAZ BOARD BACKS $280M PLAN

A board meeting of Hungarian utility Tigaz, whose control was recently
acquired by Italy's Italgas and Snam (IGR 289/4 and see separate
story), has named Eugenio Lancellotta as chairman and approved a five
year, $280m business plan. Lancellotta is already deputy chairman and
managing director of Turin-based Italgas. Among other appointments,
Biagio Marino is Tigaz managing director and Enrico Monti finance
director, while Janos Szalai is operations manager. At the time of
purchase of control last month, the Italgas-Snam consortium said it
planned to increase annual sales from 2.3 Bcm to 3 Bcm and the number
of customers from 800,000 to 1m.



